00:47:05,969 --> 00:47:07,554
Forgive me. Please?

781
00:47:07,638 --> 00:47:09,806
-Spare me!
-I'm sorry.

782
00:47:09,890 --> 00:47:12,476
-You've got to spare me.
-I'm fucking sorry!

783
00:47:12,559 --> 00:47:14,478
-Forgive us, or we're dead.
-It's okay.

784
00:47:14,561 --> 00:47:15,812
Honestly, it's okay.

785
00:47:16,313 --> 00:47:17,856
Don't do this. It's fine.

786
00:47:17,940 --> 00:47:20,442
No, please spare me. I'm really sorry.

787
00:47:27,574 --> 00:47:28,533
Hyeong-ju.

788
00:47:32,371 --> 00:47:33,705
Are you really okay?

789
00:47:58,063 --> 00:47:59,022
I'm sorry.

790
00:48:33,056 --> 00:48:34,975
If you don't want classes, don't come.

791
00:48:35,058 --> 00:48:37,686
If you don't want to study, then don't.
It's your life.

792
00:48:38,437 --> 00:48:39,271
But…

793
00:48:42,107 --> 00:48:43,734
don't get in someone else's way.

794
00:48:46,153 --> 00:48:49,781
Don't assume your minute
is the same as another person's.

795
00:48:51,074 --> 00:48:52,617
It may feel the same now…

796
00:48:58,582 --> 00:49:01,376
but later, it'll have made
decades of difference.

797
00:49:12,262 --> 00:49:13,305
Understood, you punks?

798
00:49:13,972 --> 00:49:14,806
Yes, sir!

799
00:49:15,807 --> 00:49:17,476
Why are you guys silent? Understood?

800
00:49:17,559 --> 00:49:18,685
Yes, sir!

801
00:49:33,575 --> 00:49:36,578
<i>I will report</i>
<i>on the results of the ERPB's work.</i>

802
00:49:37,412 --> 00:49:40,582
Through our inspector's efforts
at Guun High-Tech High School,

803
00:49:40,665 --> 00:49:44,002
the ERPB has resolved
violations of the right to learn.

804
00:49:44,086 --> 00:49:45,587
To prevent any recurrence,

805
00:49:45,670 --> 00:49:49,966
we will take the following actions
alongside related departments.

806
00:49:50,050 --> 00:49:50,884
TATTOO REMOVAL CLINIC

807
00:49:50,967 --> 00:49:54,346
<i>From now on,</i>
<i>tattoos will be banned in all schools.</i>

808
00:49:55,222 --> 00:49:57,390
If you move,
your bare skin will get burned.

809
00:49:58,600 --> 00:50:02,062
<i>Motorcycles will be prohibited</i>
<i>on school grounds.</i>

810
00:50:02,562 --> 00:50:05,649
YOU'LL BE A GREAT MECHANIC
YOUR FRIEND, GEUN-DAE

811
00:50:11,404 --> 00:50:13,532
<i>Should a student join or attempt to join</i>

812
00:50:13,615 --> 00:50:17,619
<i>bullying gangs, school gangs,</i>
<i>or any organized crime groups,</i>

813
00:50:17,702 --> 00:50:19,412
<i>they will face adult charges</i>

814
00:50:19,496 --> 00:50:22,040
<i>and penalties under the law</i>
<i>on organized crime groups.</i>

815
00:50:22,791 --> 00:50:27,462
Finally, we will work
with the Ministry of Justice and the MSIT

816
00:50:27,546 --> 00:50:30,465
to continuously take action on
millennial and Gen Z gangs

817
00:50:30,549 --> 00:50:33,135
that recruit members through social media.

818
00:50:33,635 --> 00:50:35,512
<i>We at the ERPB</i>

819
00:50:36,096 --> 00:50:39,766
<i>will do our best to uphold</i>
<i>students' rights to compulsory education.</i>

820
00:50:39,850 --> 00:50:40,684
Turn off the TV!

821
00:50:40,767 --> 00:50:41,810
Yes, sir.

822
00:50:41,893 --> 00:50:43,562
Oh wow!

823
00:50:43,645 --> 00:50:46,189
You walked out of there,
and now you're here.

824
00:50:47,482 --> 00:50:50,819
Minister, don't you think
you're on TV too much lately?

825
00:50:50,902 --> 00:50:52,654
Why? Do you want to be on it?

826
00:50:52,737 --> 00:50:55,574
That's not what I meant.
You just seem to be enjoying it.

827
00:50:55,657 --> 00:50:56,908
Am I not allowed to?

828
00:50:56,992 --> 00:50:58,285
Of course you are.

829
00:50:58,368 --> 00:51:01,163
Did you see that?
"Those who disrupt learning, listen up."

830
00:51:01,246 --> 00:51:03,748
"Don't get in the way
of compulsory education." So cool.

831
00:51:05,083 --> 00:51:09,045
May I interrupt your conversation
for a brief moment?

832
00:51:09,129 --> 00:51:09,963
What is it?

833
00:51:10,046 --> 00:51:14,050
While carrying out my duties recently,
I incurred a few expenses.

834
00:51:14,134 --> 00:51:16,011
Yes, you should claim expenses.

835
00:51:16,094 --> 00:51:17,220
What are they?

836
00:51:17,721 --> 00:51:19,598
I was mugged

837
00:51:20,724 --> 00:51:22,434
about three times in total.

838
00:51:22,517 --> 00:51:24,060
Oh, mugged?

839
00:51:24,769 --> 00:51:26,563
They took 40,000 won in cash

840
00:51:26,646 --> 00:51:29,900
and 500 won for premium coffee
at a vending machine.

841
00:51:29,983 --> 00:51:31,902
And outside the workshop,

842
00:51:31,985 --> 00:51:35,989
a pair of sneakers worth about 125,000 won
called Nike Air Force…

843
00:51:36,573 --> 00:51:39,701
Let's just say white Nike shoes
were taken from me.

844
00:51:39,784 --> 00:51:43,872
And I was microwaving
a 2,200-won Uiseong garlic sausage

845
00:51:43,955 --> 00:51:46,208
at the school snack bar,

846
00:51:46,291 --> 00:51:48,293
and that was taken too.

847
00:51:48,376 --> 00:51:51,880
So I ultimately spent 167,700 won

848
00:51:51,963 --> 00:51:54,049
from my personal funds.

849
00:51:54,132 --> 00:51:57,302
Would I be able to claim those?

850
00:51:57,886 --> 00:51:58,762
Sure.

851
00:51:59,512 --> 00:52:01,556
Was anything else taken?

852
00:52:01,640 --> 00:52:03,350
Well…

853
00:52:03,850 --> 00:52:05,352
MEDICAL BILLS…

854
00:52:05,435 --> 00:52:06,937
No, nothing else.

855
00:52:08,146 --> 00:52:10,315
I see. Go ahead and claim the expenses.

856
00:52:10,899 --> 00:52:12,025
Thank you, sir.

857
00:52:16,029 --> 00:52:17,405
Should I buy you a sausage?

858
00:52:18,240 --> 00:52:20,450
Pardon? No, sir.

859
00:52:20,533 --> 00:52:23,787
-It's fine.
-Have one of those Uiseong garlic things.

860
00:52:23,870 --> 00:52:24,871
-Go on.
-Hey.

861
00:52:25,622 --> 00:52:26,456
He's just a kid.

862
00:52:26,539 --> 00:52:29,125
-But he said he had it taken--
-That's enough.

863
00:55:17,043 --> 00:55:20,004
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim

